metadata.name: Lichen #55
metadata.description:
It is estimated that over 5% of the earth's land surface is covered by lichen and some have been alive for over 5000 years. Since beginning this project we have been interested to notice lichen growing everywhere, all around us, on walls and stones, pavements and trees, usually pale and unobtrusive but sometimes gloriously colourful.

This artwork is created on 3 layers, a primary, secondary and interactive layer.
To interact first use a key:
'v' for vertical;
'h' for horizontal;
'r' for round;
'l' for loose;
then click on the canvas and a patch of lichen will be drawn in the chosen style.

Clicking 'n' will create a new blank canvas to draw on.

Clicking 'y' will return to the original layers but you will need to reload in order to draw on this layer.

Clicking 'u' will delete the interactive layer and clicking again will delete the secondary layer.

To redraw it will be necessary to reload the artwork but clicking 'o' before drawing will allow you to draw on a new layer over the top of the existing work.

Keys 4, 5, 6 & 7 will render at larger sizes.

Most palettes are subtle and/or natural but there are 3 increasingly rare palettes, Rainbow, Monochrome and Golden.
Original artworks which include overlapping are also rare.

metadata.name: (un)connected #271
metadata.description:
A playful collection for #fxhashturnsone.

(un)connected
the older we get,
the more we risk losing the connection,
with who we once were,
what we still are,
colorful,
loving and caring,
playful,
connected

be
childlike


Thank you very much for this amazing first year. 


Controls:

- Press [p] to save the current image
- Press [1-5] to render and save the image in a higher resolution (1 = low; 5 = high)

Made with p5. All primary sales go to Savepakistan. Royalties go to the Processing Foundation.

Tested with Safari Version 16.1 (18614.2.9.1.12) and Chrome Version 107.0.5304.87. Browser updates can affect the future behavior.

metadata.name: Gravures #243
metadata.description:
Gravures are digital paintings inspired by many influences. They recreating abstract nature using horizontal lines and a touch of randomness, resulting in a natural and organic appearance.

------------

In live mode :  
 - Press ’s’ to save a png - A4 (21 x 29.7cm) is the default size 
- Add an url parameter to choose between physical sizes (cm) : 20x30, 30x40, a4 or a3. 
At the end of the url you can add « &size=20x30 », « &size=a3 » …

metadata.name: the endless dance #59
metadata.description:
“We thought of life by analogy with a journey, a pilgrimage, which had a serious purpose at the end, and the thing was to get to that end, success or whatever it is, maybe heaven after you’re dead. But we missed the point the whole way along. It was a musical thing and you were supposed to sing or to dance while the music was being played.” ― Alan Watts

Controls
spacebar: pause/unpause
mousedown: overdraw
x key: clear canvas

enjoy the dance

metadata.name: GuageTiles #10
metadata.description:
An interactive tiled pattern is generated with the fxhash which determines two features at random.

"groundsState" value determines a base configuration and is sampled uniformly at random in the range 0 to 1.

"spectralGap" determines the color of the pattern and comes in three types::
'low' (30%) is monochrome
'mid' (60%) is small hue range
'high' (10%) is a large hue range

*click/touch & hold/move* the canvas to charge the pattern and change the flux mode of the tiles.
*release* the canvas and the pattern decays back to its "groundState" value.

metadata.name: ThetaStar #17
metadata.description:
A "ThetaStar" is generated through an Iterated Function System determined by the fxhash with one main feature 'Theta' corresponding to an angle value in radians sampled uniformly at random in the range 2.5 < Theta < 3.0.

**Click / Touch** the canvas to reset and watch the "ThetaStar" gradually radiate in full spectrum.
The visually daring may **Rapidly Click / Touch** for an enhanced strobe like effect.
